					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8089661#post-4029424</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8089661/scp-4837#post-4029424</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 19 Oct 2018 22:54:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It seems our voterbase is having more and more trouble recognizing poor writing, given the reception of this work. We should expect more than passable in the mainlist.</p> <p>This is actively bad writing.</p> <p>There is nothing to the character beyond a half-hearted gimmick of Hollywood-medieval speech. It rides on the basic premise without elaborating on the character or its ability in any significant way, essentially reiterating the description in the dialogue in the most vanilla manner possible. It's lolrandom, without really capitalizing on the disparate nature of its form and function.</p> <p>I can tolerate, and even enjoy silly random scenarios and traits, but really only when individual works excell at it. This is, at its heart, an absolutely forgettable article. A significant overhaul would be needed to bring this up to snuff.</p> <p>-1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
